lead_paragraph: Although some of the most reviled Mubarak-era figures were barred from the election, several other officials or close relatives have seen their political fortunes restored.

headline.main: Egypt’s Parliament Prepares for Session With Some Familiar Names
headline.print_headline: Egypt’s Parliament May Be Missing Prominent Faces, but the Names Are Familiar

abstract: Egyptian Parliament is set to be seated for first time in three years, and many of country's  lawmakers either served during Pres Hosni Mubarak's reign or are relatives of those who flourished under Mubarak; critics say return of many of same faces is indication that Parliament is merely window dressing for Pres Abdel Fattah el-Sisi's autocratic rule.
